==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bourbon
<hw>Bour"bon</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the castle
and seigniory of <ets>Bourbon</ets> in central France.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A member of a family which has occupied several
European thrones, and whose descendants still claim the throne of
France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A politician who is behind the age; a ruler or
politician who neither forgets nor learns anything; an obstinate
conservative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bourbonism</ent>⟦br⟧
